# BodaSure Frontend — React, Portals & SDK Usage

## Stack & Conventions

- **React 18** + **Vite 6** + **Tailwind CSS** + **shadcn/ui** (Radix) in `src/components/ui/`
- Routing in `src/App.jsx` — do not register routes outside this file without updating portal nav in `src/lib/staffNav.js`
- Data fetching: `@tanstack/react-query` via `src/lib/query-client.js` where applicable; many pages use direct `base44.entities` calls
- Path alias: `@/` maps to `src/`

## SDK Access (Single Client)

- Import SDK only from `src/api/base44Client.js`: `import { base44 } from '@/api/base44Client'`
- **Never** instantiate a second Base44 client in components
- Entity CRUD: `base44.entities.<EntityName>.filter/create/update/get/delete`
- Backend logic: `base44.functions.invoke('<functionName>', payload)` — check `res.data` shape per FEATURE_CONTRACTS.md
- Auth: `base44.auth.me()`, `base44.auth.updateMe()`, `base44.auth.logout()`, `base44.auth.redirectToLogin('/app')`
- Realtime: `base44.entities.<Entity>.subscribe(callback)` — always unsubscribe on unmount

## Auth Context Rules

From `src/lib/AuthContext.jsx`:

- Use `useAuth()` hook for `user`, `refreshUser`, `logout`, `navigateToLogin`
- **Always call `refreshUser()` immediately after any `base44.auth.updateMe()`** in the rider app
- Login redirect destination is always `/app` — never the current URL
- Do not bypass AuthProvider loading gates in authenticated routes

## Portal Layout & RBAC

| Portal | Layout | Role gate |
|---|---|---|
| Rider `/app` | `RiderLayout` | any authenticated user |
| County `/county` | `StaffLayout accent="emerald"` | `county_admin` |
| SACCO `/sacco` | `StaffLayout accent="blue"` | `sacco_admin` |
| Merchant `/merchant` | `StaffLayout accent="emerald"` | `merchant_admin` |
| Agent `/agent` | `StaffLayout accent="orange"` | `field_agent` |
| Stage `/stage` | `StaffLayout accent="blue"` | `stage_admin` |
| Admin `/admin` | `StaffLayout accent="orange"` | `super_admin` or `bodasure_staff` |

- Portal access helpers live in `src/lib/portals.js` — use `hasPortalAccess` and `getAccessiblePortals`
- `StaffLayout` accepts `requiredRole` as string or array; `super_admin` bypasses all checks

## Onboarding UI (7 Phases)

Phase detection: `getOnboardingPhase(user, vehicles, groupMembers, wallet)` in `src/lib/onboarding.js` returns 0–6.

| Phase | Component area | Completion gate |
|---|---|---|
| 0 | `PhasePersonal*` (form, OTP, PIN, success) | profile fields + wallet tier ≥ 1 active |
| 1 | `PhaseBike` | vehicle with plate_number |
| 2 | `PhaseMapBike` | sub_county_id or stage_id on vehicle |
| 3 | `PhaseStage` | stage_id on vehicle |
| 4 | `PhaseSacco` | GroupMember exists |
| 5 | `PhaseVerification` + `verification/*` | user.verification_complete |
| 6 | `CompletionScreen` | onboarding_complete |

**Locked UI behaviors:**
- Completed phases render **read-only** with `ReadOnlyBanner` — accept `readOnly` prop on all Phase* components
- Profile saves via `updateMe()` **before** wallet init — wallet failure must not lose profile data
- OTP resend must propagate new `requestId` via `onRequestIdUpdated` callback to parent orchestrator
- Phone/ID uniqueness checks on blur — hard-block duplicates; handle HTTP 429 without blocking form permanently
- User-facing strings say **"BodaSure Wallet"**, not "SasaPay"

Orchestrator entry: `src/pages/rider/Profile.jsx` delegates to Phase* components.

## Home Dashboard Pattern

`src/pages/rider/Home.jsx` is an **orchestrator** — data loading + state here; rendering delegated to:

- `HomeWalletActivateGate`, `HomeHero`, `HomeStatusBanners`, `HomeOwnerActions`, `HomeNavGrid`

Home reads: `user.onboarding_complete`, `user.verification_complete`, `user.kyc_status`, `user.pending_group_id`, `user.group_rejection_reason`, wallet status/tier, KycDocuments, GroupMembers, Vehicles.

Wallet gate shows when `wallet.status !== 'active' || wallet.tier === 0`.

## Service Access Gating

Use `checkServiceAccess(service, { user, wallet, bikes, countyLive })` from `src/lib/serviceAccess.js` before rendering locked features:

- `lipisha` — wallet active
- `lipa_county` — wallet active + bike registered
- `lipa_owner`, `wallet_send`, `wallet_withdraw`, `services` — wallet active + Tier 2 (KYC verified)

Show `TierLimitGateSheet` or gate UI — do not silently fail.

## Payments UI

- C2B flows (Lipisha, deposit): use `initiateStkPush()` from `src/lib/payments.js`
- Internal wallet transfers may still use mock path — do not assume live SasaPay for lipa_county/lipa_owner/chama without checking `payments.js`
- Normalize phones via `normalizePhone()` from `src/lib/phone.js` before any payment call

## File Size & Component Structure

Per DECISIONS.md stabilization rules:

- **No file exceeds ~200 lines** — split into focused sub-components and shared `src/lib/` helpers
- One component = one responsibility (orchestrator vs presentational split)
- Business logic belongs in `src/lib/` (compliance, verification, onboarding, payments, phone, feeEngine) — not duplicated across pages
- shadcn/ui primitives stay in `src/components/ui/` — do not modify base UI components for domain logic

## Compliance UI

- Rider compliance page: `src/pages/rider/Compliance.jsx` uses `computeComplianceScore()` from `src/lib/compliance.js`
- Return shape: `{ score, tier, breakdown }` — tier strings: `Non-Compliant`, `Partial`, `Road-Ready`, `Fully Verified`
- Do not change tier string values (CSS class matching in ComplianceTierHero and OfficerModeOverlay)
- Admin compliance dashboard: `src/components/admin/ComplianceDashboard.jsx` — avoid N+1 queries; batch-fetch rider data in parallel

## Legacy & Redirects

- `/app/wallet/activate` redirects to `/app/profile` — wallet activation lives in Profile onboarding Phase 0
- On Profile load: silently purge legacy KycDocuments missing `provider_reference` for id_front/id_back/selfie (non-blocking)

## Frontend Change Checklist

Before finishing any frontend PR:

1. Confirm FEATURE_CONTRACTS.md callers still match your invoke payloads and response handling
2. Call `refreshUser()` after profile/onboarding saves
3. Verify portal nav paths match new routes in `staffNav.js`
4. Run relevant QA_CHECKLISTS.md section manually or describe test steps to PM
5. No placeholder code, no omitted JSX blocks, no `// ... rest unchanged`
